<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Times Now","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://iks.timesnownews.com/s/v1/img/c_en_sitepublisher.png","width":600,"height":60}},"headline":"Tata Sons, Ratan Tata helmed-Tata Trusts pledge Rs 1500 crore to combat coronavirus pandemic","description":"Tata Trust Chairman Ratan Tata and Tata Sons pledged Rs 1,500 crore to aid the nation in its fight against the coronavirus pandemic    ","datePublished":"2020-03-28T16:57:00+05:30","dateModified":"2020-03-28T22:18:40+05:30","mainEntityOfPage":"https://www.timesnownews.com/business-economy/companies/article/tata-trusts-pledges-rs-500-crore-to-combat-coronavirus/570727","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://imgk.timesnownews.com/story/TATAMISTRY.jpg?tr=w-600,h-450","height":"450","width":"600"},"author":{"@type":"Thing","name":"ET Now Digital"},"keywords":"Tata Trusts, Ratan Tata, Anand Mahindra, Corona virus outbreak , COVID-19 funds","articleBody":"New Delhi:&amp;nbsp;Ratan Tata&amp;nbsp;and Tata Sons, on Friday,&amp;nbsp;pledged a generous Rs 1,500 crores to aid the nation&amp;nbsp;in combatting the COVID-19 pandemic.&amp;nbsp;\r\n\r\nTata Trusts which is helmed by Ratan Tata&amp;nbsp;committed&amp;nbsp;Rs 500 crore and&amp;nbsp;Tata Sons, the principal holding company of the salt-to-software conglomerate,&amp;nbsp;announced another Rs 1,000 crores&amp;nbsp;to manufacture ventilators, protective gear, Covid-19 testing kits and facilities to treat infected persons.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe&amp;nbsp;development comes at a time where the nation&amp;nbsp;is reeling under the dual crises&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;coronavirus outbreak and lockdown to curb its transmission.&amp;nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe&amp;nbsp;funds will be utilised&amp;nbsp;for Personal Protective Equipment for&amp;nbsp;medical personnel on the frontlines of the outbreak, respiratory systems for treating increasing cases, kits to increase per capita testing, setting up modular treatment facilities for infected patients among others.\r\n\r\n&quot;The COVID 19 crisis is one of the toughest challenges we will face as a race. The Tata Trusts and the Tata group companies have in the past risen to the needs of the nation. At this moment, the need of the hour is greater than any other time,&quot; Ratan Tata,&amp;nbsp;Chairman said in a statement on Twitter today.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&quot;In this exceptionally difficult period, I believe that urgent emergency resources need to be deployed to cope with the needs of fighting the COVID 19 crisis, which is one of the toughest challenges the human race will face. Today, The Tata Trusts continue their pledge to protect and empower all affected communities and is committing Rs 500 crore...&amp;nbsp;&quot; he added.\r\n\r\nHe said that Tata Sons and the Tata group companies are joined by committed local and global partners as well as the government to fight this crisis on a united public health collaboration platform which will strive to reach out to sections that are underprivileged and deprived.\r\n\r\nN Chandrasekaran, the Chairman of&amp;nbsp;Tata Sons, in a statement&amp;nbsp;said, &quot;in addition to the initiatives articulated by Tata Trusts, we are also bringing in the ventilators necessary and are gearing up to also manufacture the same soon in India&quot;.\r\n\r\nThe country is facing an unprecedented situation and crisis. All of us would have to do whatever it takes to alleviate and enhance the quality of lives of the communities we serve, he added.\r\n","name":"Tata Sons, Ratan Tata helmed-Tata Trusts pledge Rs 1500 crore to combat coronavirus pandemic"}</script><input data-targeting='{"page":"consumption", "lang":"en", "section":"business_companie"}' id="page-targeting-570727" type="hidden"/>



